        "title": "Browser Use replaces the legacy changelog media pipeline",
        "summary": "The Playwright- and Browserbase-based demo screenshot system is removed and replaced with an Anthropic-planned, Browser Use-driven capture flow, along with a new authenticated capture entry point in the app and server.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Removed the old changelog media publishing stack, including the publish/retry/sync GitHub workflows and the large demo-screenshot toolchain (publish-changelog-media, demo-seed-planner, demo-agent-brief, demo-browser-seed, produce-agent-demo-screenshots), trimming roughly 20k lines across ~68 files.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "888afbe54b40663a072507842a7e01418d213479"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Introduced a Browser Use-based planning pipeline: new scripts for plan-changelog-media, a changelog-media-planner library, a Browser Use trial runner, and a pipeline evaluator, wired to new BROWSER_USE_API_KEY/BROWSER_USE_MODEL env vars with Anthropic driving candidate selection before capture.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "888afbe54b40663a072507842a7e01418d213479"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Added a dedicated capture-auth path on the server (capture_auth.rs plus tests and router wiring) and a new CaptureLoginView in the interface, gated by an AURA_CHANGELOG_CAPTURE_SECRET, so automated changelog capture can sign in without touching normal user auth.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "888afbe54b40663a072507842a7e01418d213479"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Refreshed supporting docs and tooling: added a Browser Use plan doc and an Aura navigation contract/sitemap generator for the interface, while removing the demo-screenshot-pipeline doc and associated navigation-lessons fixtures.",
            "commit_shas": [
